column1: #Text=Egypt anti-government protests continue , Internet shut down

#Text=Anti-government protestors in Egypt rallying against the rule of president Hosni Mubarak took to the streets for a fourth straight day , demanding the long-time leader step down and complaining of poverty , corruption , and oppression .
#Text=The demonstrations were supposedly inspired by a popular uprising that saw Tunisian president Zine al-Abidine Ben Ali ousted from office .
#Text=A national curfew is in effect , but is being ignored by many .
#Text=Protestors in Cairo , Tuesday – the initial day of protests .
#Text=Tens of thousands of people spilled out into streets after Friday prayers today , chanting slogans like " Down , down with Mubarak " and "
